152. Maximum Product Subarray
Given an integer array nums, find a subarray that has the largest product, and return the product.
The test cases are generated so that the answer will fit in a 32-bit integer.
Note that the product of an array with a single element is the value of that element.

 
Example 1:
Input: nums = [2,3,-2,4]
Output: 6
Explanation: [2,3] has the largest product 6.

Example 2:
Input: nums = [-2,0,-1]
Output: 0
Explanation: The result cannot be 2, because [-2,-1] is not a subarray.
 

Constraints:
1 <= nums.length <= 2 * 104
-10 <= nums[i] <= 10
The product of any subarray of nums is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.

Approach:-
//Run the loop from first element and store the product
//One will store the product of elements and one will store maximum among the product

Time Complexity: O(n2)

Solution:-
class Solution {
    public int maxProduct(int[] nums) {
        int maxProd=1;
        int max=0;
       //Handling edge cases if array has one element return the element
        if(nums.length == 1)
        {
           return nums[0];
        }
       //max amd maxProd two variable to keep product
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
             //max=0;
             maxProd=1;
            for(int j=i;j<nums.length;j++){
                 maxProd *= nums[j];
                 if(maxProd > max){
                    max=maxProd;
                 }
            }
        }
        return max;
    }
}
